;; ADR-2607182410: named-capability counterpart of capability-policy.edn --
;; capability-named.kotoba writes `(cap-call :identity/sign value)` instead
;; of a magic integer. `:identity/sign` resolves (at parse time, via
;; resources/kotoba/compiler/capability-registry.edn) to id 1, so the policy
;; below is identical in shape to capability-policy.edn -- admission.cljc
;; never sees the keyword, only the resolved [:cap/call 1] effect.
{:allow #{[:cap/call 1]}}
